07:27.424 --> 07:28.265
Oh, I don't know.

07:28.325 --> 07:30.107
I just kind of got carried away with myself.

07:30.187 --> 07:31.949
Maybe I could buy one from you at some point.

07:34.151 --> 07:35.332
Well, you don't need three, do you?

07:36.293 --> 07:38.195
No, but the government has them.

07:38.215 --> 07:38.275
Oh.

07:38.795 --> 07:44.643
Do those belong to you, or will they go elsewhere?

07:45.004 --> 07:47.147
Well, one of them will be mine.

07:47.667 --> 07:48.949
Well, that's yours.

07:48.969 --> 07:50.431
I'm still going to find my Brindley.

07:50.511 --> 07:51.733
I don't know.

07:51.753 --> 07:54.157
You know, one of them is questionable.

07:56.280 --> 07:57.722
In their mind or in their minds?

07:57.742 --> 07:58.363
In their minds.

08:00.005 --> 08:01.026
So I may have one.

08:01.046 --> 08:02.288
I don't know.

08:02.656 --> 08:05.419
No, I thought you said you had three.

08:05.840 --> 08:07.082
Well, I did have three sets.

08:07.102 --> 08:08.904
I understand, but you don't really.

08:08.924 --> 08:11.527
You have one.

08:11.547 --> 08:12.168
One that's yours.

08:12.809 --> 08:13.269
Oh, yeah.

08:13.770 --> 08:16.293
Yeah.

08:16.313 --> 08:17.675
Ma and Pa Gas.

08:18.296 --> 08:18.496
Yeah.

08:22.140 --> 08:24.383
You need a fan belt on this, my friend.

08:24.403 --> 08:24.964
Yeah.

08:25.785 --> 08:27.207
It only does that after dark.

08:27.227 --> 08:27.607
I don't know.

08:27.647 --> 08:28.729
I work on it in the daytime.

