10:44.804 --> 10:46.026
We can choose.

10:47.153 --> 10:58.529
to conform to the external things to a greater or less degree, or we choose not to.

10:58.549 --> 11:09.023
I don't know, maybe in somebody else's perspective, from the outside looking at me, because we all live within ourselves, you know.

11:09.044 --> 11:11.627
Maybe to some people it appears that way.

11:11.647 --> 11:13.089
To me it appears.

11:13.109 --> 11:15.152
You're living here and now in 1991.

11:17.478 --> 11:29.846
Well, kind of in contrast to it in some respects, but everything I have and do is all right to me, you know.

11:29.866 --> 11:32.773
Doesn't seem strange, but isn't that the way it is for all of us?

11:32.993 --> 11:34.918
Yep.

11:34.938 --> 11:35.098
Sure is.

11:40.124 --> 11:42.386
How many miles would you say this car has got on it?

11:42.406 --> 11:43.587
Oh, it doesn't have too many.

11:43.687 --> 11:44.688
The odometer's broke.

11:44.708 --> 11:45.269
I bought it.

11:45.289 --> 11:46.050
It had 21,000.

11:46.310 --> 11:48.512
It's got probably 60,000.

11:48.692 --> 11:49.533
It was one owner.

11:49.553 --> 11:50.594
You only had 21,000?

11:50.874 --> 11:53.157
Yeah, I bought it for 15 years.

11:53.357 --> 11:54.097
That's amazing.

